President Obama will be hosting the second White House Science Fair on February 7th. The event will showcase the winners of various science, technology, engineering, and math (STEM) competitions from across the country. The President will also announce initiatives aimed at helping more students excel in math and science and earn degrees in these subjects. The fair will feature exhibits of student work, including breakthrough research and new inventions. President Obama hosted the first White House Science Fair in 2010 as part of his Educate to Innovate campaign. He believes that students who excel in STEM subjects should be recognized for their achievements.